ParticleGS — Licensing
======================

This artifact contains code under several licenses. The layering is:

1. Authors' code — Gaussian-Splatting Research License (INRIA/MPII)
------------------------------------------------------------------
All code written by the ParticleGS authors (the `particlegs/` package,
`pipelines/`, `experiments/`, `scripts/`, `configs/`, `data/`,
`verify_results.py`, and the build/reproduction tooling) is a derivative
work of the INRIA/MPII "gaussian-splatting" codebase and is therefore
distributed under the same terms: the Gaussian-Splatting Research
License (non-commercial research and evaluation use; contact
stip-sophia.transfert@inria.fr for other uses).

Full license text: submodules/diff-gaussian-rasterization/LICENSE.md

2. Vendored third-party components (keep their own licenses)
------------------------------------------------------------
- submodules/diff-gaussian-rasterization — Gaussian-Splatting Research
  License (INRIA/MPII); see LICENSE.md therein. Its bundled
  third_party/glm is MIT ("The Happy Bunny License" / MIT).
- submodules/simple-knn — Gaussian-Splatting Research License
  (INRIA/MPII); see LICENSE.md therein.
- submodules/fused-ssim — MIT License (Copyright (c) 2024 Rahul Goel);
  see LICENSE therein.

3. Fetched at install time (not shipped in this repository)
------------------------------------------------------------
install.sh clones and builds the baseline compressors into SZ3/ and
LCP/; both are BSD-licensed (Copyright UChicago Argonne, LLC — see
copyright-and-BSD-license.txt in each cloned tree).

4. Data (downloaded on first run, not shipped)
----------------------------------------------
- HACC particle subset — from SDRbench (https://sdrbench.github.io);
  see SDRbench for dataset terms.
- FIRE-2 L172 snapshot — CC BY 4.0 (Feedback In Realistic
  Environments / FIRE collaboration public data release).
